  "notes": "Calabrian. Southern Italo-Romance of Calabria. Internally diverse: N. Calabria patterns with the Neapolitan dialect continuum, S. Calabria with Sicilian. Key features: (1) Vowel reduction to [ə]. (2) Metaphony. (3) Retroflex consonants in S. Calabria (-LL-→[ɖː], TR→[ʈɽ]). (4) Strong Greek substrate influence. Griko (Italo-Greek) still spoken in pockets (Fanciullo 2015, Rohlfs 1966).",
  "quality": "research",
